133 Non dimandai “Che hai?” per quel che face 134 chi guarda pur con l’occhio che non vede, 135 quando disanimato il corpo giace;
136 ma dimandai per darti forza al piede: 137 così frugar conviensi i pigri, lenti 138 ad usar lor vigilia quando riede».

query.result:
**English:**
133 Do not ask "What is it?" for what he does 134 who looks only with the eye that does not see, 135 when the body lies dispirited;
136 but ask in order to give strength to your foot: 137 thus it is necessary to prod the lazy, slow 138 to use their waking time when it returns.
**Sanskrit:**
133 Na pṛcchasi "Kim idam?" yasya kartavyam 134 Paśyati kevalam cakṣuṣā yena na dṛśyate, 135 Yada śarīram acetanam śete;
136 Api tu pṛcchasi yena pādayoḥ śaktir dīyate: 137 Evam ālasān mṛdun prakopayitum ucitam, 138 Ye svapnakāle prāpte na prayatante.
